Harper vs. Burks. Held, that the service was too late. January 6, 1885.

The judge’s certificate to a bill of exceptions was dated “March term, 1884,” of Olay ton superior court. From an agreement of counsel, it appears that the March term adjourned on March 12. “ Due and legal ” service of the bill of exceptions was acknowledged on April 8:

Writ of error dismissed.
